  <title>Web Browser Technology - History</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>History of Web Browsers</h1>
    <p class="tagline">How browsers developed from simple tools into powerful platforms.</p>

    <nav>
      <ul class="menu">
        <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="history.html">History</a></li>
        <li><a href="features.html">Modern Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="concepts.html">Key Concepts</a></li>
        <li><a href="references.html">References</a></li>
        <li><a href="about.html">About</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Early Development</h2>
      <p>
        The first web browser, WorldWideWeb, was created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1990.
        It was designed to help users access and connect documents over the internet.
        Later, browsers like Mosaic helped make the web more visual and user-friendly,
        which increased public interest in the internet.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>The Browser Wars</h2>
      <p>
        In the 1990s and early 2000s, Netscape Navigator and Internet Explorer
        competed heavily for users. This period became known as the browser wars.
        Competition led to fast growth, but it also created compatibility problems
        because websites did not always work the same across browsers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Modern Era</h2>
      <p>
        Today, browsers such as Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge,
        Apple Safari, and Opera focus on speed, security, standards support, and
        user privacy. Browsers now serve not only as tools for reading webpages,
        but also as platforms for streaming, communication, gaming, and web apps.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Browser Timeline</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Year</th>
            <th>Browser/Event</th>
            <th>Importance</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>1990</td>
            <td>WorldWideWeb</td>
            <td>First web browser created</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>1993</td>
            <td>Mosaic</td>
            <td>Made the web easier for the public to use</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>1994</td>
            <td>Netscape Navigator</td>
            <td>Became one of the earliest popular browsers</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>1995</td>
            <td>Internet Explorer</td>
            <td>Started strong competition in browser market</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>2008</td>
            <td>Google Chrome</td>
            <td>Changed browser design with speed and simplicity</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>
  </main>

